Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art showing figures of nine Nile river boats, one cow and one unidentified shape. Boat figures are all upright with bow to left, infilled with pecking. Rightmost two boats, one above the other, have no oars, the others have multiple oars raised up with the exception of most ornate boat at lower left, with ten oars down and ostrich-like figure with extra protuberance at neck above, upright and facing left, as is cow figure to right of this boat, pecked in outline and infilled with sparse pecking. Unidentified figure (cow?) stands at bottom centre. A 10cm scale has been fitted at the bottom of the image. El-Kanais, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
